            <h2>The Tradition of Rivalry</h2>
            <p>College football is all about rivalries, many of them spanning over a century. These rivalrys go beyond the game; they are cultural events that divide families, towns, and even states.</p>
            
            <img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/nflleague/image/private/t_new_photo_album/league/yjceyixe8r4y04nwnb0i.jpg" alt="A college football game being played in a packed stadium." class="stadium-image">
            <figcaption>A packed stadium on a Saturday afternoon.</figcaption>

            <h3>The Top Conferences</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>SEC (Southeastern Conference) - Known for its dominance and deep-south tradition.</li>
                <li>Big Ten Conference - Home to massive stadiums and historic programs.
                    <ul>
                        <li>Michigan Wolverines</li>
                        <li>Ohio State Buckeyes</li>
                        <li>Penn State Nittany Lions</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Big 12 Conference - Historically known for high-powered offenses.</li>
                <li>ACC (Atlantic Coast Conference) - Strong programs, especially in the Southeast.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

